Executive Summary & Technical Conclusions. 

1.Data Profile and IntegrityCorpus Dimension: The source dataset originally contains 1,597 observation rows spread across 27 distinct attributes (pp. 1-2).
Data Sparsity: Severe missing data constraints were identified during data auditing. 
  Operational identifiers like reviews.
  userCity, reviews.userProvince, and sizes contained 0% data density (1,597 missing values) (p. 4). 
  Crucial targets like reviews.rating lacked 420 values (p. 4).
Cleaned Subset: Removing null elements strictly from our primary feature spaces (reviews.rating and reviews.text) left a robust, highly verified subset of 1,177 clean textual records for down-stream modeling (p. 5).
2. Sentiment Skew and Market Bias
  Polarity Breakdown: Mapping the numeric text reviews to categorical labels revealed a massive, positive customer sentiment skew (p. 6):
    Positive (Ratings 4–5): 977 reviews (83.0%)
    Neutral (Rating 3): 124 reviews (10.5%)
    Negative (Ratings 1–2): 76 reviews (6.5%)
3. Structural Text Insights
  The Length-Rating Paradox: Calculating the Pearson correlation coefficient between parsed text length (review_length) and the numeric score produced a value of \(r = 0.0013\) (p. 10).
  Strategic Takeaway: This near-zero value proves that review length is completely decoupled from product satisfaction (p. 10). A highly frustrated customer venting about a failure writes roughly the same number of words as an enthusiastic advocate reviewing a daily-use device.
4. Advanced Semantic Mining
  Topic 1 (Hardware Ergonomics): Surface vocabulary clusters like headphone, apple, like, and dont highlight user interactions with portable peripheral items (p. 13).
  Topic 2 (Smart Ecosystem Integration): Strong thematic grouping of terms like great, tap, speaker, echo, and love maps directly to hands-free automation tech and smart-home audio configurations (p. 13).
  Topic 3 (Utility & Gifting Contexts): Clusters around gift, prime, tv, and recommend identify user buying drivers, emphasizing e-commerce delivery perks and transactional gift purchases (p. 13).
  Unsupervised Clustering Engine: Running K-Means partitions the text dynamically, sorting 731 reviews into Cluster 0, 369 reviews into Cluster 1, and 77 reviews into Cluster 2 (p. 13). 
  This maps closely onto our global sentiment weights, verifying structural consistency between raw ratings and algorithmic text parsing.
